    "body": {
        "divs": [
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Her finger provided the drama, ploughing a traumatic furrow across the well-worn path."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": ""
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The ants scurried in confusion, and Samar Dev watched them scrabbling fierce with the insult."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": ""
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The soldiers with their heads lifted and mandibles opened wide as if they would challenge the gods."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": ""
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Or, in this case, a woman slowly dying of thirst."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": ""
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The deliverance of discord into otherwise predictable, truncated and sordid lives seemed a worthwhile thing."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": ""
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Well, perhaps not worthwhile, but certainly interesting."
            },
            {
                "type": "photo",
                "file": "",
                "caption": ""
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "God-like thoughts, then, to mark her last day among the living.<br><br><i>- Steven Erikson, The Bonehunters, Malazan Book of the Fallen</i>"
            }
        ]
    }
}


